{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"C\n    \n      Lazy-Load Elections (Recommended)\n      Backend: New services/elections.py + routers/elections.py with POST /api/elections. Completely independent from rep lookup. New election research pipeline (2-3 sections) with its own endpoint POST /api/election-research.\n      Research reuse: Candidate research uses existing POST /api/research unchanged. Election-level research is new but follows the same patterns (background task, polling, incremental sections).\n      Frontend: React Router with /reps and /elections. Rep data loads immediately on search. Election data loads only when user clicks the Elections tab — lazy fetch. This keeps the happy path fast.\n      \n        Pros\n          Zero impact on existing rep lookup speed\n          Clean separation — elections is a self-contained feature\n          Election tab can show a loading state independently\n          Easiest to build incrementally and test in isolation\n        \n        Cons\n          Two API calls from frontend (one per tab)\n          Slight delay when switching to Elections tab first time","choice":"c","id":null,"timestamp":1774391731652}
